1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,890
The overwhelming majority of really successful people work much longer than 40 hours a week,

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,010
and you don't hear them complain of overwork.

3
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:14,610
Successful people have their eyes focused on a goal, and this provides energy.

4
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:16,690
The point is this.

5
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:24,209
Energy increases, multiplies, when you set a desired goal and resolve to work toward that goal.

6
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:33,570
Many people, millions of them, can find new energy by selecting a goal and giving all they've got to accomplish that goal.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,890
Goals cure boredom.

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,010
Goals even cure many chronic ailments.

9
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:43,410
Let's probe a little deeper into the power of goals.

10
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:49,649
When you surrender yourself to your desires, when you let yourself become obsessed with a goal,

11
00:00:49,760 --> 00:00:55,810
you receive the physical power, energy, and enthusiasm needed to accomplish your goal.

12
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:59,970
But you receive something else, something equally valuable.

13
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:06,770
You receive the automatic instrumentation needed to keep you going straight to your objective.

14
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:14,290
The most amazing thing about a deeply entrenched goal is that it keeps you on course to reach your target.

15
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:16,128
This isn't double talk.

16
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,810
What happens is this.

17
00:01:18,079 --> 00:01:24,050
When you surrender to your goal, the goal works itself into your subconscious mind.

18
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:27,490
Your subconscious mind is always in balance.

19
00:01:27,599 --> 00:01:33,649
Your conscious mind is not, unless it is in tune with what your subconscious mind is thinking.

20
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:41,490
Without full cooperation from the subconscious mind, a person is hesitant, confused, indecisive.

21
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:48,530
Now, with your goal absorbed into your subconscious mind, you react the right way automatically.

22
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:52,530
The conscious mind is free for clear, straight thinking.

23
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:56,770
Let's illustrate this with two hypothetical persons.

24
00:01:56,960 --> 00:02:01,889
As you listen, you'll recognize these characters among the real people you know.

25
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,450
We'll call them Tom and Jack.

26
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:08,690
These fellows are comparable in all respects except one.

27
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:11,409
Tom has a firmly entrenched goal.

28
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,930
Jack does not.

29
00:02:13,359 --> 00:02:16,849
Tom has a crystal clear image of what he wants to be.

30
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:21,810
He pictures himself as a corporation vice president ten years hence.

31
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:29,649
Because Tom has surrendered to his goal, his goal through his subconscious mind signals to him saying,

32
00:02:29,839 --> 00:02:32,129
do this or don't do that.

33
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:34,609
It won't help get you where you want to go.

34
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:40,210
The goal constantly speaks, I am the image you want to make real.

35
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:43,890
Here is what you must do to make me real.
